  "prompt": "Strike the odd one out and explain your rationale: a) jane austen b) george eliot c) charlotte bronte d) homas hardy?",
  "response": "The odd one out is **Thomas Hardy**.\n\nRationale: Jane Austen, George Eliot, and Charlotte Bronte are all primarily known for their contributions to the Victorian novel and are often categorized as authors of classic literature focusing on social issues and personal relationships, particularly in the context of women's roles in society. \n\nIn contrast, Thomas Hardy, while also a prominent Victorian author, is distinct in that his works often incorporate themes of fatalism, tragedy, and the harsh realities of rural life, as well as a more pessimistic worldview. Additionally, Hardy is sometimes considered a bridge to modernism and is known for a more critical view of societal norms, especially regarding class and gender, compared to the other three authors, who generally align more closely within the traditional Victorian context.",
